            <p>
                <strong>2005-08-20</strong><br />
                The phpMyFAQ Team would like to announce the availability of
                <a href="/download">phpMyFAQ 1.5.0</a>. After almost one year of development
                and seven release candidates this new version features support for MySQL, PostgreSQL, Sybase and MS SQL
                databases. phpMyFAQ 1.5.0 has also support for LDAP and additionally there's an experimental support for
                IBM DB2 databases. Now FAQ articles can be added to more than one category and we support search engine
                friendly URLs with mod_rewrite. The template engine is faster and the PDF export was completly
                rewritten. Beside the better RSS support you can export your complete FAQs to XML, XHTML, DocBook XML
                and PDF.
            </p>
